8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to S.P. 723,
9 L.D. 1840, “An Act to Amend the Maine Medical Use of Cannabis Act”
10 Amend the amendment by striking out all of sections 1 and 2.
11 Amend the amendment in section 6 in the last 3 lines (page 2, lines 23 to 25 in
12 amendment) by striking out the following: "This section does not preclude the office from
13 also offering registration and renewal forms through an online registration portal or similar
14 system."
15 Amend the amendment by striking out all of section 7.
16 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
17 section number to read consecutively.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This amendment removes the provision in Committee Amendment "A" that prohibits
2200 the Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office of Cannabis Policy from
2211 requiring registrants to make attestations on registration and renewal forms regarding
2222 conduct authorized under the Maine Medical Use of Cannabis Act, except where explicitly
2233 authorized by law. It removes a provision in Committee Amendment "A" specifying that
2244 the Office of Cannabis Policy is not precluded from offering registration and renewal forms
2255 through an online registration portal. It removes the appropriations and allocations section.
